news.title: Reclaimed 24 acres of encroached land in Yamuna floodplain: DDA to NGT
news.para: The report said that though the DDA was continuously engaged in the removal of encroachments, it was sometimes tough to protect or fence the area after a demolition drive was carried out.

news.title: Bengaluru: BBMP extends deadline for 5% rebate on property tax till May 31
news.para: ​​​However, under Section 144(8) of the BBMP Act, 2020, the BBMP has the authority to recommend an extension of the rebate period to the government through a notification.

news.title: Strategic buyers and investors scouting for insolvency-affected cement assets
news.para: Investors and strategic buyers are also closely observing the ongoing insolvency cases against companies, including Jammu & Kashmir Cements, Kirtiman Cements & Packaging and Gujarat-based Dhara Cements.

news.title: PNB Housing Finance to resume project financing soon: MD
news.para: The lender's asset quality improved to 1.08% at the end of FY25 as compared with 1.5% a year back. It aims to bring down gross NPA below 1% this year.

news.title: Maharashtra consumer commission orders builder to pay Rs 12 lakh for delay, missing amenities
news.para: On hearing both sides, the commission held that the builder's failure to deliver possession on time and non-fulfilment of promised facilities constituted a clear deficiency in service under the Consumer Protection Act.

news.title: Prestige Group launches residential project in Ghaziabad
news.para: The first phase of Prestige Group's residential project called Oakwood and Mulberry- together represents a gross development value (GDV) of over ₹9,000 crore.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh RERA removes 12 employees over integrity issues
news.para: Sanjay Bhoosreddy, chairman, UP-RERA said, "An affidavit of integrity is also taken from every officer and employee in RERA. CCTV cameras have been installed in all the rooms in RERA office."

news.title: Sales in India’s top eight property markets up by 18% in FY25
news.para: Despite the slowdown in new supply, unsold inventory remained under control at around 8 lakh units, with a healthy inventory overhang of just 19 months.

news.title: MIS portal launched to provide information about land acquisition projects in Bihar
news.para: Additional chief secretary Deepak Kumar Singh, who was present on the occasion, said many land acquisition projects were going on in the state.

news.title: Madhya Pradesh HC orders status quo over land encroached by BMC
news.para: This land was allegedly encroached upon by the Bhopal Municipal Corporation (BMC), the women and child development department, and the public health department of the state govt.

news.title: Compass sues US-based Northwest Multiple Listing Service over marketing rules
news.para: Compass in its lawsuit in the Seattle federal court on Friday said Northwest Multiple Listing Service was trying to protect its dominance by overly controlling how sellers market their homes, in violation of U.S. antitrust law.

news.title: Punjab lags behind in smart city project execution: SBI report
news.para: Launched by Prime Minister Narendra Modi on June 25, 2015, the Smart Cities Mission was designed to transform 100 cities across India into citizen-centric, sustainable urban centres.

news.title: RHB set to introduce two residential schemes for middle-income groups in Jaipur
news.para: The housing schemes in Mansarovar are meant for two middle-income groups. The two schemes – named Ganga and Gulmohar – will have 160 flats of 2-BHK and 3-BHK categories.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body extends rebate scheme for property tax payment till May 30
news.para: Between April 8 and 28, the AMC received advance property tax from over 3.95 lakh residents, with a collection of Rs 482.89 crore. The total rebate amounted to Rs 52.78 crore.

news.title: Embassy REIT posts 10% rise in NOI in FY25
news.para: The board of directors of Embassy Office Parks Management Services (EOPMSPL), manager to Embassy REIT, declared distributions of ₹5,384.04 million / ₹5.68 per unit for the quarter ended March 31, 2025.

news.title: Lucknow: LDA forms committee to address Basant Kunj’s issues
news.para: Officials said that launched in the 1990s, the Basant Kunj scheme covered 1,353 acres spread across ten sectors (A to J), involving land of around 800 farmers and inhabitants

news.title: SC orders CBI probe against builders in NCR after fraud on homebuyers
news.para: ​A bench of Justices Surya Kant and N Kotiswar Singh found a prima facie nexus between renowned banks and builders in NOIDA, Gurugram, Yamuna Expressway, Greater Noida, Mohali, Mumbai, Kolkata and Allahabad.

news.title: Ambuja Cements' net profit dips 15.71% in Q4 FY25
news.para: Ambuja Cements' net consolidated total income stood at ₹10,461.87 crore in Q4 FY25, a growth of 14.62 per cent from ₹9,127.45 crore it recorded in the similar quarter last year. It's annual volume was up by 10% at 65.2 Mn T.

news.title: Developers pivot to offer GCCs more than just offices
news.para: Setting up a GCC in India involves creation of an ecosystem comprising physical infrastructure, people and business operations, said Arjun Aggarwal, managing director at Bhartiya Urban.

news.title: Gensol pulled out of DLF office deal a month before Sebi order
news.para: Gensol had signed letter of intent (LoI) in 2024 but conveyed to the developer a month ago that it cannot sign the final agreement.
